# Sprint 2 Milestone: Accounts, Moderation & Deployment - Walkthrough

I have completed the core features for Sprint 2, including user accounts, content moderation, image sharing, API documentation, and production readiness.

## Changes Made

### S2-1 to S2-3: Accounts & Moderation
- **Database Schema**: Added [User](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/UserProfilePage.jsx#6-129), [Report](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/src/controllers/moderation.controller.js#4-36), and `ModerationAction` models. Moved to Prisma Enums for all categorical fields.
- **Backend Implementation**: Integrated Google OAuth with Passport.js and implemented a full moderation lifecycle with [requireAdmin](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/server/src/middleware/auth.js#156-192) guards.
- **Frontend Implementation**: Added a [ModerationPage](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/ModerationPage.jsx#4-118) admin dashboard and [ReportButton](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/components/ReportButton.jsx#4-92) components across the UI.

### S2-4: Screenshot Sharing Flow
- **Themed Export**: Users can now export completed logs as PNG images with Minimal, Nocturne, or Parchment themes using `html-to-image`.
- **Integration**: Added sharing capabilities to the [LogDetailPage](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/client/src/pages/LogDetailPage.jsx#37-380) for completed works.

### S2-5: Prisma Enum Refactoring
- **Objective**: Improved data integrity by replacing raw string fields with formal Prisma `enum` types (`LogStatus`, `Category`, `AccessMode`, etc.).
- **Consistency**: Synchronized backend Zod schemas and frontend translation maps with the new Enum structure.

### S2-6: Public API Documentation
- **Tooling**: Integrated `swagger-jsdoc` and `swagger-ui-express`.
- **Scope**: Fully documented Logs, Auth, Moderation, Reactions, and User Profile APIs.
- **Accessibility**: Available at `/api-docs` on the server.

### S2-7: Production Deployment & CI Integration
- **Infrastructure**: Created [render.yaml](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/render.yaml) Blueprint to automate the deployment of the PostgreSQL database, Node.js API, and Static UI.
- **CI/CD**: Verified that GitHub Actions correctly handles linting and testing for both client and server on every PR.
- **Environment**: Provided a comprehensive [.env.example](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/.env.example) and resolved all lingering TypeScript/Environment issues in [prisma/seed.ts](file:///Users/danielkalo/Documents/CS%207180%20-%20Vibe%20Coding%20%28Python%29/Project%202%20-%20Collective%20Unconscious/prisma/seed.ts) by installing `@types/node`.
- **Database Consistency**: Applied missing migrations to synchronize the local environment with the partner-merged Reactions API and the Enum refactor.

